The U.S. National Association Wheat Growers ( NAWG ) urged Reagan administration offer Soviet Union wheat export enhancement program ( eep ) .
In letter Agriculture Secretary Richard Lyng , NAWG stated `` strong support '' eep offer Moscow .
`` We believe solid case continues exist Soviet EEP eligibility , recently announced reported Soviet purchase U.S. corn indicate Soviet willingness purchase U.S. grain competitively priced , '' NAWG said .
`` Consequently , believe important renew U.S. eep offer reasonably possible ensure mutual adherence term U.S.-Soviet grain agreement , '' letter said .
